The paper deals with a pricing problem in which items have limited supply and customers have budgets and preferences. This falls under the category of algorithmic game theory (cs.GT) and computational social choice (cs.DS). The paper also proposes approximation algorithms using local search and LP rounding, which are common techniques in approximation algorithms (cs.AI). The problem involves assigning prices and choosing customers to maximize revenue, which is a common problem in economics and mechanism design (cs.EC). Finally, the paper involves analyzing the performance of algorithms, which is related to theoretical computer science (cs.IT).
